---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base>
  <article>
    <header>
      <h1>Notes from Hyper-Dimensional Spelunking</h1>
      <time datetime="2018-08-24">August 24, 2018</time>
    </header>

    <section>
      <p>
        The thing about working at the intersection of technology and creativity is that you often find yourself
        in strange territories that don't appear on any map. It's like being a spelunker, but instead of caves,
        you're exploring the vast multidimensional space of possibility.
      </p>

      <p>
        Each project becomes an expedition into uncharted territory. You pack your tools—code, design principles,
        a healthy skepticism, and an unreasonable amount of optimism—and venture forth into the unknown. Sometimes
        you discover beautiful crystalline structures of logic that take your breath away. Other times you get
        thoroughly lost in recursive loops that seem to fold back on themselves infinitely.
      </p>

      <p>
        The most fascinating discoveries happen in those liminal spaces between disciplines. When you're writing
        code that generates art, or designing interfaces that feel almost alive, or building systems that learn
        to surprise their creators—that's when the real magic happens. It's messy and unpredictable and absolutely
        exhilarating.
      </p>

      <p>
        These are just notes from one such expedition. The coordinates might not be entirely accurate, and the
        terrain shifts constantly, but maybe they'll be useful to fellow travelers venturing into their own
        unexplored dimensions.
      </p>
    </section>
  </article>
</Base>

<style>
  article {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 8rem;
  }

  header {
    text-align: center;
  }

  article p {
    max-width: 50ch;
    font-size: var(--proseFontSize);
    margin-bottom: var(--proseParagraphGap);
    margin-inline: auto;
  }
</style>
